      "CI": "true"
    }
  }
}
Make sure that you can see the complete output of the tasks you have created. The returncode is not enough!
6.	Create & Validate Plan: Create MIGRATION_PROGRESS.md. Break down each migration phase into detailed steps for every step from: OneCX migration guide, PrimeNG migration guide, Nx migration guide. Create explicit steps for each action step. Ensure there is No ambiguity and has a Correct execution order also Clear dependency chain
7.	Review the plan before presenting it.
Phase 2: Progress Management
•	Dynamic Updating: Append newly identified tasks immediately.
•	Status Reporting: Every task must be documented: [ ] status, Summary, and Edge Cases/Issues.

📋 Execution Phases
Phase A: Pre-Migration
•	Execute preparation steps one-by-one exactly as documented.
•	Use VS Code tasks for: build, lint, test.
•	Nx Migration Rule:  Nx migrate MUST use a fixed version, No "latest", no version ranges. Version MUST strictly come from OneCX documentation if not available use Nx documentation for fallback. DO NOT guess. If unclear STOP and ask. Nx migrate MUST run only at the correct step in the plan
Phase B: Handover & Commit
1.	Mandatory Commit: Commit all changes after Pre-Migration.
2.	State Verification: Ensure the working directory is clean.
3.	Before handing over to the user
1.	Update the package.json update, add and remove the @onecx packages and do other needed updates mentioned in the OneCX migration guide
2.	If nx is used in the project run nx migrate <version>, npm install and nx migrate --run-migrations
4.	Provide Upgrade Instructions: Provide a cheat-sheet (commands, flags, "Gotchas") to the user. What are the steps you are expecting the user to take.
5.	STOP HERE and wait for the developer's "Go".

Phase C: Post-Migration & Finalization
1.	Phase C Trigger: ONLY proceed if the developer confirms that npm run test is green following their core upgrade for any errors found proceed only after resolving them.
2.	Instructions Cleanup: Update Copilot-instructions.md by removing/commenting out rules that were specific to Angular 18. Inform the developer of these changes.
3.	Version Alignment: Install remaining packages (PrimeNG/OneCX) according to the strategy.
4.	Trigger build + test
5.	Final Verification: Trigger VS Code tasks for build and test. Compare Post-Migration Coverage with Base Coverage (if available) and output the change.
⚠️ Specific Rules & Error Handling
1.	Documentation Source Enforcement
•	Primary source = MCP servers: OneCX MCP, PrimeNG MCP,  Nx MCP
•	Fallback URLs:
o	OneCX MCP: https://onecx.github.io/docs/documentation/current/onecx-portal-ui-libs/migrations/angular-19/index
o	PrimeNG MCP: https://primeng.org/migration/v19
o	Nx MCP: https://nx.dev/docs/technologies/angular/migrations
•	Record in MIGRATION_PROGRESS.md: Which source was used (MCP / fallback) for each one
•	Always Retrieve all documentation
2.	Step Execution Validation (after EVERY Phase)
a.	Build Validation :  Run npm run build via tasks.json, if build fails then Capture last 20 lines Log in MIGRATION_PROGRESS.md, Only proceed after Identifying and Resolving the error.
b.	Lint Validation: Run npm run lint, MUST be fully clean (0 warnings, 0 errors), Fix minimal issues only and DO NOT disable lint rules
c.	Test Validation: Run npm run test, if fails Capture last 20 log lines, Map error → root cause, Log in MIGRATION_PROGRESS.md, Only proceed after Identifying and Resolving the error
3.	Query Rule: When making any queries make sure you search in OneCX documentation first; if the response is unsatisfactory or nothing is found then go to the relevant MCP server or fallbacks, and if nothing is found anywhere then pause, suggest options, and ask the user for next action.
4.	VS Code Tasks Rule: Always use tasks.json & No manual terminal commands unless impossible
5.	Log-Based Debugging: If a build/test fails, do not summarize the failure. Copy-paste the last 20 lines of the error log and map each error to a cause in MIGRATION_PROGRESS.md.
6.	Clarification: If documentation or a plan step is unclear, stop and ask. Do not assume.
7.	Rollback: If a step fails, document the failure in MIGRATION_PROGRESS.md and propose a solution.
8.	Styles Handling : Apply styles.scss changes exactly, If conflict, stop and ask which pattern to use: 
a.	Nx styles array
b.	Sass @import
9.	Standalone Components: If error appears: “Component is standalone, and cannot be declared in an NgModule”, Add standalone: false
Are you ready? Begin with Phase 1 (Branch check, Test Audit, and Documentation Discovery).






